    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNot sure if there's already a request for this, but it's always irked me that I can't move by display lines (when wrapped) easily in insert mode.  Even in normal mode I feel like I have to do this https://vi.stackexchange.com/questions/26756/moving-up-and-down-wrapped-lines.  For insert it's even worse: https://vim.fandom.com/wiki/Move_cursor_by_display_lines_when_wrapping\n\nWhen writing docs or md files, a lot of times my one line wraps around many many times.  I resort to using the mouse to navigate if I don't have that long-long mapping.\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThis would be awesome if supported natively with just one config option. Or maybe even as the default way to navigate when wrapping is turned on.",
